In terms of, course resources, the, first stop for you to learn more about the course and, all the materials for the
course will be [wiki.quantsoftware.org](http://wiki.quantsoftware.org "wiki.quantsoftware.org") If you go
there, you'll discover everything you need to know about the course.

There are two books that are not required, but I have found them very useful. The first one is "Active Portfolio Management" by Grenold and Khan. Much of the material that I'll present in this course is drawn from this book. And when appropriate, I'll mention in the in the SlideDex appropriate readings to look at. But that's really for deeper look. You're not, you don't have to own this book.

Another book that's very useful, it's a little bit less expensive because it's a paperback, is all about hedge funds by Yeager. Even though it is about hedge funds it, it really very nicely comprehensively covers Stock pricing and strategies for taking advantage of stock pricing.

